<!--DOCTYPE para SYSTEM "/usr/share/sgml/docbook/xml-dtd-4.1.2/docbookx.dtd"--><ns2082:section xmlns:ns2082="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.design.patterns.classical.structural.composite.intent">

  <ns2083:title xmlns:ns2083="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Intent</ns2083:title>
  <ns2084:para xmlns:ns2084="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Typically there are two core intents when using the compsite pattern:
    <ns2085:orderedlist xmlns:ns2085="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns2086:listitem xmlns:ns2086="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2087:para xmlns:ns2087="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        To represent tree structures supporting recursive part-whole relationships.
      </ns2087:para></ns2086:listitem>
      <ns2088:listitem xmlns:ns2088="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns2089:para xmlns:ns2089="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        To facilitate services which are realized recursively through the structure.        
      </ns2089:para></ns2088:listitem>
    </ns2085:orderedlist>
  </ns2084:para>
  <ns2090:para xmlns:ns2090="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    These can be shown in a generic use-case view for the pattern:
  </ns2090:para>
